# Essential Windows CMD and PowerShell Commands
(Windows 10) - as 11 is not safe 

## Getting Started
Windows has two main command-line interfaces:

- **CMD (Command Prompt)**: Classic Windows shell for basic commands and scripting.
- **PowerShell**: Advanced shell for automation, scripting, and system management.

---

## Common CMD Commands 

### Navigation & File Management

- `dir` ‚Äî List files and folders
- `cd <folder>` ‚Äî Change directory
- `cls` or `clear` ‚Äî Clear the screen
- `copy <src> <dest>` ‚Äî Copy files
- `move <src> <dest>` ‚Äî Move/rename files
- `del <file>` ‚Äî Delete files
- `mkdir <folder>` ‚Äî Create directory
- `rmdir <folder>` ‚Äî Remove directory
- `type <file>` ‚Äî View file contents
- `ren <old> <new>` ‚Äî Rename file
- `exit <to exit the terminal>`

